Intuition
after looking at problem i thought i can solve this problem with 2 pointer pattern , i will need 2 pointers i , j , one pointer scans the array and the other keeps track of the position where the next non-zero element should be placed. the idea is to collect all non-zero elements at the front while pushing zeros to the end.

Approach
Initialize i = 0 (position for next non-zero)
Iterate j from start to end of array
If nums[j] != 0:
swap nums[i] and nums[j]
increment i
j always moves forward

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def moveZeroes(self, nums: List[int]) -> None:
        """
        Do not return anything, modify nums in-place instead.
        """
        i = 0
        for j in range(len(nums)):
            if nums[j] != 0:
                nums[i] , nums[j] = nums[j] , nums[i]
                i+=1
